2026 Regular Session
HOUSE BILL NO. 1167
BY REPRESENTATIVE GLORIOSO
HIGHWAYS: Designates certain portions of highways in Louisiana
1 AN ACT
2 To designate the elevated portion of Louisiana Highway 433 in Slidell, Louisiana as the
3 "Emile 'Uncle Tobe' Galatas Bridge"; to designate a portion of United States
4 Highway 11 in Pearl River, Louisiana as the "Captain Steven Gaudet, Jr. Memorial
5 Highway"; to provide for implementation; and to provide for related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. The elevated portion of Louisiana Highway 433 from Dubee Pena Road
8 to Rivet Drive in the city of Slidell, Louisiana, parish of St. Tammany, shall be known and
9 is hereby designated as the "Emile 'Uncle Tobe' Galatas Bridge".
10 Section 2. The portion of United States Highway 11 from the Dr. T.J. Smith, Sr.
11 Expressway to Louisiana Highway 41 in the city of Pearl River, Louisiana, parish of St.
12 Tammany, shall be known and is hereby designated the "Captain Steven Gaudet, Jr.
13 Memorial Highway".
14 Section 3. The Department of Transportation and Development or its contractors are
15 hereby directed to erect and maintain appropriate signage reflecting these designations
16 provided local or private monies are received by the department equal to the department's
17 actual cost for material, fabrication, mounting posts, and installation of the signage, not to
18 exceed the sum of seven hundred fifty dollars per sign for the "Emile 'Uncle Tobe' Galatas
19 Bridge" and the sum of two thousand two hundred fifty dollars per sign for the "Captain
20 Steven Gaudet, Jr. Memorial Highway".
